==English==

===Etymology===
A variant of {{m|en|see a man about a dog}}, from the implied context of seeing someone about a bet on a horse race.

===Verb===
{{head|en|verb}}

# {{lb|en|slang|idiomatic|euphemistic}} {{non-gloss definition|Used in place of a real explanation when excusing oneself for a short period of time, particularly to use a toilet.}}
#: {{ux|en|I'll be back in [[two shakes of a lamb's tail]]. I've just got to visit the [[ladies' room]] to '''see a man about a horse'''.}}

